      "message": "There is the 3rd option.\nWe might have stndDefined events without the schemaReference. \nThe field is optional, someone can declare stndDefined events w/o schemaReference.\n\nPerhaps we can tell:\n1. stndDefined events are checked only\n2. schemaReference is optional in the stndDefined, if absent the validation result is success for such an event\n3. If the openAPI description indicated in schemaReference field of stndDefined event is present in the schema-map (or in the externalSchemaRepo), thhen the validation result is successful as well.",
